            "title": "Sweden Deploys Jas Fighters to NATO Nuclear Exercise",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>For the first time, Sweden is sending its Jas 39 Gripen fighter jets to participate in NATO's annual nuclear exercise, Steadfast Noon, which begins next week.</p><p>\n\nThe purpose of the exercise is to ensure the alliance's capability to carry out nuclear missions in the event of a conflict.</p><!-- Article --><p>\n\n“Nuclear deterrence is a component of NATO's overall deterrence strategy, ultimately aimed at guaranteeing the security of allied nations. In an increasingly uncertain world, NATO must maintain a credible nuclear capability to prevent attacks on the alliance. Steadfast Noon plays a crucial role in ensuring this,” said Prime Minister Ulf Kristersson.</p><p>\n\nForeign Minister Maria Malmer Stenergard and Defense Minister Pål Jonson held a press briefing regarding the proposal titled \"Swedish Contribution to NATO's Deterrence and Defense in 2026.\"</p></div>",
